#==============================================================================
# 
#                               Sample UBBCONFIG
#
# UBBCONFIG file template for integrating TAP/CICS with TUXEDO.
#
# To enable security, uncomment all of the lines in this file that begin
# with AUTH or SECURITY.
#
# Replace the <bracketed> entries with the appropriate values.
#
# <hostname>
#       Refers to the host (node) name of your machine, which is the name
#       returned by the command:
#           $ uname -n
#
# <TUXDIR>
#       Refers to the location where you installed TUXEDO.
#       The default location is "/usr/tuxedo".
#
# <APPDIR>
#       Refers to the fully qualified directory name where your
#       TAP application runs.
#
# <TUXCONFIG>
#       Refers to the fully qualified binary version of the TUXEDO
#       configuration file.  The file itself is normally called
#       "tuxconfig".
#
# <APP.ENV>
#       Refers to the fully qualified filename defining the environment
#       to be established on behalf of your application.
#       This file must define the environment variables used by TAP.
#       The file "app.env" has been provided as your default.
#       If you use this file, remember to fully qualify its pathname.
#       For example: "/<TCXINSTALLDIR>/sys/app.env".
#
# <TUXIPCKEY>
#       A unique number assigned to your installation of TUXEDO.
#
# <REGION>
#       The unique name of the region, i.e., the resource name used for the
#       entire TAP region within the TUXEDO domain.
#
# <SUBREGION>
#       The unique name of the subregion, i.e., the resource name used for the
#       host name within the TAP region.
#
# [Distributed]
